    <stitle>HYDRO-MAX II BRAKE MONITOR SYSTEM - DESCRIPTION - DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE SWITCH</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE SWITCH</title>
        <para>The differential pressure switch provides input to the Hydro-Max monitor and thus turns on the warning
            light, alarm, and booster pump when a significant difference in pressure between the front and rear master
            cylinder halves is sensed. This switch contains normally open contacts.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
